{% set pageTitle = "Hero" %}
{% set pageSection = "Design system" %}
{% set subSection = "Components" %}
{% set pageDescription = "Use Hero at the top of a page when users need a clear introduction, optional supporting media, and one primary next step." %}
{% set theme = "Content presentation" %}
{% set dateUpdated = "July 2026" %}

{% extends "app-layout.njk" %}

{% block breadcrumb %}
  {% include "../_breadcrumb.njk" %}
{% endblock %}

{% block bodyContent %}

  <h2>When to use Hero</h2>
  <p>Use Hero once at the top of a page when users need a short, high-level introduction and a clear next step.</p>
  <p>Hero can include optional supporting media. Keep the copy brief and the call to action focused.</p>

  <h2>When not to use Hero</h2>
  <p>Do not use Hero on low-level content pages where users are trying to find specific information quickly.</p>
  <p>Do not use Hero more than once on the same page.</p>

  <h2>How to use Hero</h2>
  <p>Use the <code>brand</code> theme by default and switch to <code>dark</code> when the page needs the darker colour mode. Use the <code>free</code> variant for an open split layout or <code>boxed</code> when the content needs white containment.</p>
  <p>Hero supports at most 1 primary button and 1 secondary text link. The button is the primary call to action. The text link is the lower-emphasis secondary action.</p>
  <p>If you use media, provide meaningful alt text when the image carries information. If the image is decorative, set it as decorative so assistive technology ignores it.</p>
  <p>Hero defaults to a <code>section</code> root. Use the root override only when the page structure already provides the surrounding landmark or section semantics.</p>

  <h2>Examples</h2>

  <h3>Brand free variant</h3>
  {{ designExample({
    group: "components",
    item: "hero",
    type: "default"
  }) }}

  <h3>Dark free variant</h3>
