  <h3>Decoration and Tile pattern</h3>
  <p>Hero decoration is built with the <a href="/design-system/components/tile-pattern">Tile pattern</a> primitive. Hero owns the pattern rows, columns, placement and theme mapping so each Hero instance keeps the canonical treatment.</p>
  <p>The public Hero API lets you turn decoration off with <code>showDecoration: false</code>. If a new Hero treatment needs different tile types, colours or pattern dimensions, update the Hero component implementation using Tile pattern rather than configuring every Hero instance separately.</p>

  <h3>Accessibility</h3>
  <p>Keep the Hero heading semantic level correct for the page, which is typically <code>h1</code> for the primary page introduction.</p>
  <p>Check the focus order when both actions are present, and make sure the media alt text or decorative treatment matches the purpose of the image.</p>

{% endblock %}
